# Architecture Rules

See full spec: `docs/architecture-rules.md`

## Directory Structure

```
src/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ features/<FeatureName>/   # components/, screens/, hooks/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ components/               # shared UI
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ navigation/               # navigators + types.ts
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ services/                 # API layer
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ store/                    # Zustand global state
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ hooks/                    # shared custom hooks
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ utils/                    # pure helpers
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ constants/                # colors, spacing, typography
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ types/                    # shared TypeScript types
```

## Naming

- Components/Screens ‚Üí `PascalCase`
- Hooks ‚Üí `camelCase` starting with `use`
- Constants ‚Üí `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
- Feature dirs ‚Üí `PascalCase`, others ‚Üí `kebab-case`

## Layer Rules

- Screens ‚Üí never call fetch/axios directly
- Services ‚Üí no React hooks
- Stores ‚Üí serialisable state only
- Components ‚Üí no business logic

## TypeScript

- `strict: true` ‚Äî no `any`, use `unknown` + type guards
- Explicit return types on all functions
- `interface` for object shapes; `type` for unions

## Anti-Patterns

- ‚ùå HTML elements (`div`, `span`) ‚Äî use `View`, `Text`, `Pressable`
- ‚ùå Inline styles ‚Äî use `StyleSheet.create`
- ‚ùå Relative imports beyond 2 levels ‚Äî use `@` aliases
- ‚ùå `&&` conditional render with non-boolean left side
- ‚ùå Business logic in screen components
